<br>
I had fun grouping with Eyee and AC in howling stones a short while back. I wanted to make some minor points.<br>
<br>
If other guilds had previously gone out of order, I could understand that you feel kind of ganged up on Eyee. Perhaps you thought no one would mind. That it was no big deal. Obviously, this is not the case. Something similar happened to me a long time ago, when I first joined Triad....<br>
<br>
I was 35 or so and had spent 30+ hours camping the ac during one Fri/Sat with only 4 hours sleep. Suddenly, he popped. My partner who was helping me sent tells screaming at me NUKE IT NUKE IT NUKE IT which I did. Unfortunately, under the stress of the moment, I did not notice that the ac had been engaged at the time. I got the experience. The Planeswalkers (Siawns old guild) was very upset with me, needless to say. Even tho I had the ring, I was mortified. I felt so bad. The thrill of getting jboots for the first time was tarnished by what had happened. Odo got involved. It was ugly and messy.<br>
<br>
So I got on an alternate character and went back the next day to help the unfortunate soul who had lost the jboots to me the night before, under the guise of &quot;collecting spider silks for tailoring.&quot; It just so happened that the ac spawned near me and I took it down, for this fellows jboots. I helped him get the jboots in Lake Rathe and then revealed my identity to him. I apologized to him and to his guild.<br>
<br>
I was not pressured by anyone to do this in any way- I did it on my own to make amends to those who felt I had wronged them ( which I probably did ).<br>
<br>
To sum it up, an apology which is back up by actions goes a long way to soothe hurt feelings. You may want to consider this option, Eyee =).<br>
<br>
Take care,<br>
